HEADWORD: Prescutum
<hw>Pre*scu"tum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Prescuta</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Pr⟦ae⟧-</er>, and <er>Scutum</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The first of the four pieces composing the dorsal part, or tergum,
of a thoracic segment of an insect. It is usually small and
inconspicuous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

